d Poverty in China ENERGY AND POVERTY IN CHINA Challenges and the Way Forward C Sources UNFPA (2006); IEA (2006); and UNDP (2006) hina is the world\u2019s most populous country with more than 1.3 billion people. Approximately 60 percent of this population lives in rural areas (UNDP 2006). In terms of its total area, China is also among the largest countries in the world, covering about 9.6 million square kilometres. Over the last 30 years, developments in China have brought about enormous advances in the standard of living for a large proportion of the population, including the rural poor. According to official statistics, the number of rural people living in extreme poverty dropped from 250 million in 1978 to 28 million in 2002. Based on the international poverty line benchmark of US$1 of income per day, the number of China\u2019s poor is estimated to have dropped from around 490 million in 1990 to 88 million in 2002 (UNDP 2004)1. Furthermore, the average income has leapt from US$280 in 1985 to US$1,290 in 2005 (NBS 2005).", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "617ac06d-c022-4642-b558-54f843244808": {"__data__": {"id_": "617ac06d-c022-4642-b558-54f843244808", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-and-poverty-china", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Energy and Poverty in China", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/energy-and-poverty-china", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "0957117c2d867808673545765c946c6f3895429c74ff40b1